'''Bobby Berns''' (December 10, 1895 &ndash; July 22, 1980)<ref>[http://www.oldestlivingprofootball.com/19891980necrology.htm 1989-1980 Necrology at Oldest Living Pro Football Players]</ref> was a professional [[American football]] player who played [[offensive lineman]] for six seasons for the [[Dayton Triangles]].<ref>[http://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/B/BernBo20.htm Bobby Berns NFL & AFL Football Statistics - Pro-Football-Reference.com]</ref>

